   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,423:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:      │              (manual run)
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,425:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:      ▼
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,451:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Posts (auto)
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,452:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:   Comments (manual)
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,454:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step-by-Step Guide
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,456:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 1 — Verify Docker is installed
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,479:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker --version
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,481:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose version
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,484:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Make sure both commands return a version number. If not, install Docker first.
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,489:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 2 — Configure Reddit API credentials
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,490:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Edit the 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,491:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .env
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,493:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  file in the project root:
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,495:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,496:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,498:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: REDDIT_USER_AGENT=your-app-name
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,499:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: TARGET_SUBREDDITS=all
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,502:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: To get credentials, create an app at: https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps/
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,504:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 3 — Build and start all services
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,506:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose up -d --build
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,510:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This will build and start: Zookeeper, Kafka, HDFS (NameNode + DataNode), Reddit Producer, Flink Processor, and
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,512:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: HDFS Writer.
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,514:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The first build may take a few minutes to download images and install dependencies.
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,518:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 4 — Verify all services are running
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,519:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose ps
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,521:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Wait until all services show as 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,523:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: running
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,526:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  or 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,529:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: healthy
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,530:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: .
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,533:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 5 — Watch the producer collecting posts in real-time
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,536:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose logs -f reddit-producer
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,538:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You should see posts being streamed from Reddit. Press 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,539:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ctrl+C
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,542:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to exit the logs (the producer keeps running in the
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,543:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: background).
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,544:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: To watch other services:
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,546:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose logs -f flink-processor
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,548:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose logs -f hdfs-writer
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,551:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 6 — Let the producer collect posts
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,553:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Leave the pipeline running. The longer it runs, the more posts are collected.
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,554:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,556:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A few minutes = tens of posts
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,559:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,560:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A few hours = hundreds to thousands of posts
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,563:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 7 — Fetch comments for collected posts (manual)
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,565:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When you are ready, run:
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,567:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose run --rm fetch-comments
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,568:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This will:
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,570:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,572:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Read all posts collected so far from Kafka
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,573:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,575:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Skip any posts already processed in a previous run
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,576:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,578:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fetch ALL comments for each post from the Reddit API
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,580:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,582:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Publish comments to Kafka (linked to their parent post)
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,584:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,586:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Save progress to a checkpoint file
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,587:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: You can safely press 
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,589:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ctrl+C
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,595:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to stop — progress is saved after each post. Run the same command again later to
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,615:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: continue where you left off.
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,618:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 8 — Verify Kafka topics
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,620:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose exec kafka kafka-topics --list --bootstrap-server
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,622:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: localhost:9092
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,624:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Expected topics:
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,625:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,626:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reddit.posts
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,628:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,629:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reddit.comments
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,631:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,633:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reddit.posts.processed
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,634:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,636:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: reddit.comments.processed
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,639:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Step 9 — Check data stored in HDFS
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,641:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # List all files
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,644:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: docker compose exec namenode hdfs dfs -ls -R /data/reddit
   DEBUG: 2026-02-18 23:15:15,646:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: # Check total data size
